The Portfolio Committee on Public Enterprises and the Select Committee on Public Enterprises and Communications is holding a virtual joint meeting. Minister of Public Enterprises, Pravin Gordhan, is briefing the Committee on the latest developments at state-owned companies. The briefing comes a week after the National Transport Movement union announced that a decision was reached with the department to shut down the South African Airways (SAA)  and form a new airline. The SAA has been struggling financially. Government in April rejected the airline’s request for a R10 billion bailout. In January, the airline received  R3.5 billion from the Development Bank of South Africa (DBSA). Below is the briefing by Minister Pravin Gordhan:  